/*
 * This Hyperlambda snippet demonstrates how to perform an HTTP GET request to "https://microsoft.com"
 * and convert the HTML response into Markdown format. The [http.get] slot is used to fetch the content
 * from the specified URL, with an HTTP header indicating that the response should be in HTML format.
 * The [html2markdown] slot then processes the HTML content and transforms it into Markdown.
 */
http.get:"https://microsoft.com"
   headers
      Accept:text/html
html2markdown:x:-/*/content